gned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":20,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":33,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":42,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Nicholas d'Auberchicourte was born in 1295, in France, his father, Etienne III de dabridgecourt, was 31 and his mother, Mrs Etienne D'Abridgecourt, was 25. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Philippa de Hainaut. He died on 20 October 1345, in England, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1295–20 Oct 1345":"1295–20. oktoober 1345","1295–1345":"1295–1345","1296–1345":"1296–1345","1326–1358":"1326–1358","1327–1372":"1327–1372","1333–1358":"1333–1358","1342–1415":"1342–1415","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1296":"1296","1295":"1295","20 Oct 1345":"20. oktoober 1345"